result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Aquanisha S Grinnage

records.addlTxt: Jury trial - 12 person on April 11, 2023 at 09:00 am.

10:34 AM Defendant Aquanisha S Grinnage in court.  Attorney Gary J. Kryshak in court for Aquanisha S Grinnage.  Attorney Jennifer C Zima in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is requesting to set this matter for trial. Court grants and this will be set for a Jury Trial. Bond is continued. Attorney Zima puts the offer on the record. Court addresses the warrant the defendant has in Marathon County.

11:00 AM Defendant Aquanisha S Grinnage in court.  Attorney Gary J. Kryshak in court for Aquanisha S Grinnage.  Attorney Jennifer C Zima in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Officer Berger is sworn in and testifies. Testifies to being a Patrol Officer for the City of Wisconsin Rapids. Testifies to conducting a traffic stop of a gold Chevy Blazer. Testifies to following the vehicle trying to read the license plate and could see the driver didn't have his seat belt on. Testifies to the vehicle going under the speed limit, which is found to be odd. Testifies to the driver being Logan Novak and the passenger was Aquanisha Grinnage. Witness identifies the defendants in court, court recognizes. Testifies to seeing Logan not having a seat belt on. Testifies to Logan having a suspended drivers license. Testifies to asking Sergeant Fleisner and his K-9 Unit to the scene and they arrived about 10 minutes later. Testifies to the K-9 alerting to the vehicle. Testifies to a search being conducted and what was found. 
Attorney Nolan-Plutchak cross examines the witness. Testifies to having body cam and squad cam footage. 
Attorney Kryshak cross examines the witness. Testifies to how long he was following the vehicle for. 
Sergeant Fleisner is sworn in and testifies. Testifies to being a Sergeant with the Wisconsin Rapids Police Department. Testifies to being apart of this traffic stop w/ Officer Berger. 
Attorney Emily Nolan-Plutchak cross examines the witness. Witness testifies to not always being called on scene. Testifies to not being sure if he had footage or not. 

Attorney Nolan-Plutchak and Attorney Kryshak bring up they haven't received the two videos from discovery.
Final pre-trial scheduled for October 21, 2022 at 10:00 am.

NOTICE OF MOTION & MOTION TO
SUPPRESS EVIDENCE
Final pre-trial on June 28, 2022 at 11:00 am.

01:21 PM Defendant Aquanisha S Grinnage in court with attorney Gary J. Kryshak.  Jennifer C Zima appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Officer Burger is sworn in and testifies. Testifies to being a patrol officer with the city of Wisconsin Rapids. Testifies to conducting a traffic stop of a vehicle. Testifies to conducting the traffic stop due to not being able to read the license plate number and the driver not wearing a seatbelt. Testifies to the driver and the defendant being the passenger. Attorney Kryshak stipulates to identification. Testifies to a K-9 sniff and a search being conducted. Testifies to the substance that was found. Testifies to cash that was found on the other party. Testifies to testing of the substance and the results. Testifies to the amount that was found and that it is not usually an amount for personal use. 
Attorney Kryshak cross examines the witness. Testifies to how long the parties were being followed for. Testifies to where the substance was found. Testifies to what was found by the defendant. Testifies to the defendant denying knowing the cocaine was in the vehicle. 
Court finds probable cause to believe a felony was committed and the defendant committed it.
Not guilty pleas are entered. Bond is continued.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 12, 2022 at 09:00 am.
